{
  "texts": [
    "Named-Entity Recognition (NER) is a task that aims to identify and classify named entities in text data.",
    "In the context of anonymizing clinical notes, NER-based solutions have been historically used to identify and classify sensitive information, such as patients' or doctors' names, IDs, doctor's licenses, dates, phone contacts, emails, professions, hospital names, locations, zip codes, URLs, among other direct or indirect identifiers (Dehghan et al., 2015).",
    "One practical implementation of this task is Microsoft Presidio (Mendels and Balter, 2018), an openly available text anonymization tool designed to identify and remove sensitive entities from text data.",
    "This tool is composed of two main modules.",
    "The first is the analyzer, which identifies sensitive entities based on NER techniques."
  ]
}